body_html:
I traced this to FunctionBufferingResourceGetNextOp. Looks like the kernel returns an OutOfRange error to signal completion. This non-OK status triggers an abort of the CollectiveExecutor.

@mrry @rohan100jain is this expected behavior? I would have expected the error to be caught somewhere because it is not really an error.

body:
I traced this to [FunctionBufferingResourceGetNextOp](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/844074c2a8e61b744c3de2718e1c9ea7b1d2edc2/tensorflow/contrib/data/kernels/prefetching_kernels.cc#L382).  Looks like the kernel returns an OutOfRange error to signal completion.  This non-OK status [triggers an abort](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/844074c2a8e61b744c3de2718e1c9ea7b1d2edc2/tensorflow/core/common_runtime/executor.cc#L2153) of the CollectiveExecutor.

@mrry @rohan100jain is this expected behavior?  I would have expected the error to be caught somewhere because it is not really an error.
